{
  "texts": [
    "The Spatial Pyramid Pooling Network (SPPNet) was introduced to address this limitation, enabling the processing of variable-sized input images.",
    "Net employs a spatial pyramid pooling mechanism that divides the input image into pyramids of subregions, extracts features from each subregion, and pools them into a fixedsize representation that is independent of the original image dimensions.",
    "This approach enhances the model's flexibility and scale invariance.",
    "Furthermore, SPPNet allows feature extraction from multiple convolutional layers at different resolutions, facilitating improved object localization and mitigating the resolution reduction issue inherent in RCNN.",
    "By integrating multi-scale feature extraction and enabling efficient handling of variable image sizes, SPPNet significantly improves object detection models' flexibility, scalability, and robustness."
  ]
}